Function Reference/edit post « WordPress Codex
-----------

Update an existing post with values provided in \$\_POST. If you passed
the post data in an argument, that argument is treated as an array of
data keyed appropriately for turning into a post object. If post data is
not passed, the \$\_POST object is used instead.

Usage
-----

` <?php edit_post($post_data); ?> `

### Default Usage

` <?php edit_post($post_data); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$post_data` 
:   ([*object*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Object "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*)
    Default: null If not supplied, will apparently fallback to using the
    \$\_POST global variable

Return
------

 (string) 
:   Post ID

Filter
------

Examples
--------

Changelog
---------

-   Since: [1.5](/Version_1.5 "Version 1.5")

Source Code
-----------

`edit_post()` is located in `wp-admin/includes/post.php`.

